It's been a hard week for the Gauteng education department. In the past week, four pupils have died, two have been raped, several injuries at schools have been reported and motor accidents have been recorded. Department spokesperson Steve Mabona said the deaths and incidents occurred in different schools across the province. Deaths Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi sent condolences to the bereaved families.  Other incidents Mabona said the department had received reports on different unfortunate incidents some of which were not reported on time.